# Event emission

Events = domain facts that already happened. **Commands cause events** (MVP). **Gel DB is source of truth**; events are logged, not a queue.

## Emit for

User lifecycle, documents (upload/delete/reprocess/extract), concepts, index entry CRUD/state, collaboration-relevant actions.

## Do not emit for

GETs, helpers, raw queries, UI-only state, noisy transient errors.

## Naming & shape

`domain.entity.action` (e.g. `auth.user_logged_in`, `document.uploaded`). After successful DB work; **backend only**; shared `emit` helper; one event per meaningful change.

```typescript
type DomainEvent = {
  type: string;
  timestamp: string; // ISO
  requestId?: string;
  userId?: string;
  documentId?: string;
  entityId?: string;
  metadata?: object; // no secrets, tokens, or huge payloads
};
```

## MVP

Sync only; no Kafka/event sourcing. Ask: *Would an indexer, author, or publisher care?* If not, skip.
